  "prompt": "Up to what rank in GATE ECE can we expect a call from BARC for an interview?",
  "response": "The **Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC)** conducts interviews and selection for its **Graduate Engineer Trainee (GET)** and **Scientific Officer** positions based on the **GATE (Graduate Aptitude Test in Engineering)** scores. For the **Electronics and Communication Engineering (ECE)** discipline, the exact rank cutoff for an interview call can vary each year depending on factors such as:\n\n1. **Number of vacancies** available for ECE.\n2. **Number of applicants** and their performance in GATE.\n3. **Reservation policies** and category-based cutoffs.\n\nHowever, based on historical trends and general observations:\n\n- For **General/Unreserved category**, candidates with **GATE ranks within the top 200** in ECE have a high chance of receiving an interview call from BARC.\n- For **OBC/SC/ST/PwD categories**, the rank cutoff can be slightly higher (lower in rank number), depending on relaxation policies.\n\n### Important Notes:\n1. **Qualifying GATE is mandatory**, but only candidates who apply separately for BARC recruitment and meet the eligibility criteria are considered.\n2. The final selection is based on **GATE score, interview performance, and other selection criteria** set by BARC.\n3. The exact rank cutoff can vary, so it\u2019s advisable to check official BARC notifications or previous year trends for more accurate estimates.\n\nFor the most accurate and updated information, refer to the official **BARC recruitment notification** or their website.",
